    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have browned, add your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> and cook for 30 secs, then add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook until evaporated</p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then turn the heat to low and cook for 6-7 min or until the sauce has thickened, then remove from the heat and set aside – these are your <strong>peppercorn mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
